Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Half, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces. Trim the @carrot{1}, then quarter lengthways (no need to peel). Chop widthways into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a garlic press).

> Quick, easy to prep and packed with fresh ingredients, our fragrant salmon pilaf is the perfect one-pot dish.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat. When hot, add the shallot and carrot. Cook until beginning to soften and colour, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring frequently. Once softened, stir in the garlic, @ground cumin{2}, @ground turmeric{2}, @basmati rice{150} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

When your kettle has boiled, pour the @water{300%ml} into a #measuring jug{} and stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Add to the rice and bring to the boil. When boiling, lower the heat back to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}.

After 10 mins, remove the #saucepan{} from the heat and quickly pop the @baby spinach{125} into the pan, no need to stir it in. Immediately return the lid to the pan and leave covered for another ~{10%minutes} (still off the heat).

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam and the spinach will wilt.

Once the rice is cooked, add the @hot smoked salmon{150} flakes and stir in gently. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the rice between your plates. Enjoy!